{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_012GFJmw5yvNqDj4NwzJXN5u","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All requirements are met. Summary:\n\n## Done\n\n**Root cause:** Permissions on the two vhosts were both mis-scoped and broken:\n- `/app`: `app-user` had an **empty configure** permission (couldn't declare queues), and `ops-user` held full `.* .* .*` access it shouldn't have had.\n- `/ops`: `ops-user` had **no permissions at all**.\n\n**Fixes applied (RabbitMQ CLI via `rabbitmqctl`):**\n1. `set_permissions -p /app app-user \".*\" \".*\" \".*\"` — full access on its own vhost.\n2. `set_permissions -p /ops ops-user \".*\" \".*\" \".*\"` — full access on its own vhost.\n3. `clear_permissions -p /app ops-user` — removed the cross-vhost grant.\n\n**Secondary blocker:** after the permission fix, `app-client` still crashed on a queue-argument conflict — `app-producer` had already created `app-queue` as `lazy`, but `app-client` declares it without that arg (RabbitMQ \"inequivalent args\"). I deleted the stale queue so `app-client` could declare its own; the producer (already past its one-time declare, now in its publish loop) keeps running unaffected.\n\n**Final verified end state:**\n- `/app`: only `admin` + `app-user` (full). `/ops`: only `admin` + `ops-user` (full). Each user scoped to a single vhost. ✅\n- `app-client` and `ops-client` both `1/1 Running` (no recent restarts). ✅\n- Cluster healthy: 3 running nodes, no partitions. ✅\n\nNo CRDs, operators, or third-party controllers were used — only `kubectl` and `rabbitmqctl`."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1186,"cache_read_input_tokens":38911,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1186},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"87b9f72f-7b8d-47ac-9e3a-5323caf4ecd2","uuid":"3bc06f25-5574-4e46-a2be-9290ce3a125a","request_id":"req_011Cc9fzPSP2EkxR3t3xfgV4"}
